Warning: Seems like if the method is protected rather than private and it is overridden, the overriding method will be called. Thus, if you are using #invokePrivateMethod to access a private method in the superclass, you had best name your calling method something different from the method you are calling, lest the superclass method be made protected (or public) in the future. (Suggestion: prefix the name of your calling method with an underscore).
